      },
      "date": "2013-03-25 17:29:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nPlease forward declare 'struct hsm_copytool_private;' in lustreapi.h and give these functions proper prototypes without void **/void * first args.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "21f0f15cb09cf98e2cc0812ed0f983130ce88e7a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-25 18:00:51.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis structure is llapi internal only, we would like to avoid to expose it to caller (like for priv arg in llapi_changelog_start())",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "4c60d13cc2c90dbc06bf9b2e0dab5a43c5252951",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-03-25 18:08:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI understand.  Just put \"struct hsm_copytool_private;' in lustreapi.h and leave the structure definition in liblustreapi_hsm.c.  In this way nothing is exposed but basic typechecking is facilitated.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
